      "content": "Look, if we take that portal offline for 6 hours right now, the board is going to kill me. We're in the middle of the quarterly processing window and any downtime will trigger massive penalties and probably a huge backlash from customers. \n\nIs there *any* way we can just monitor the traffic and apply the fix during the scheduled window tonight instead? I need you to be 100% certain—is this an absolute \"shut it down right this second\" situation, or is there a way to mitigate the risk while keeping the site live?",
